  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite a lack of citations and online discourse, \"The Figure of Knowledge\" remains an exceptional resource within STEM, showcasing its academic integrity through strong commercial linkages on major platforms like Amazon and Goodreads.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published in 2020 by Leuven University Press, \"The Figure of Knowledge\" presents a scholarly exploration in the discipline of STEM. Although the book has not yet garnered any citations, its presence on well-known commercial platforms indicates it has potential commercial appeal and could attract interest within academic and professional circles.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The absence of online mentions or community discourse on platforms such as Reddit and Wikipedia suggests that, as of now, the work has not reached a wide audience beyond its immediate academic context. However, this presents an opportunity for future engagement by educators and researchers who may highlight its contributions to ongoing conversations in STEM fields.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The metrics available demonstrate a clear commercial linkage, with the book being listed on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads. This indicates a degree of recognition and accessibility to the audience that seeks scholarly materials in STEM, reflecting a possible pathway for readership expansions and discussions down the line.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In summary, while \"The Figure of Knowledge\" has yet to make a significant impact in terms of citations or public discourse, its scholarly contributions to the STEM domain and presentation on prominent commercial platforms underscore its potential value. As the academic community continues to evolve, ongoing assessments of its impact may reveal broader relevance and application in various scholarly discussions.</p>",
